Debugging observations:
- this can be reproduced in a room using @[email that doesn't exist]@[email_provider].[tld], in order to create a room, `canUseAllBetas` must return true (if one doesn't already have betas enabled)
- the `AddComment` response contains the account id of the newly tagged user in `targetAccountIDs` array
- the user is populated and doesn't show hidden anymore only after `OpenReport` is called which returns `personalDetailsList` data for the id observed in `targetAccountIDs` of initial `AddComment` call response:

```
{
	"onyxData": [
		{
			"onyxMethod": "merge",
			"key": "personalDetailsList",
			"value": {
				"16002717": {
					"accountID": 16002717,
					"avatar": "https://d2k5nsl2zxldvw.cloudfront.net/images/avatars/default-avatar_13.png",
					"displayName": "a.b.c@hmail.com",
					"firstName": "",
					"lastName": "",
					"status": null,
					"login": "a.b.c@hmail.com",
					"pronouns": "",
					"timezone": {
						"automatic": true,
						"selected": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"payPalMeAddress": "",
					"phoneNumber": "",
					"validated": true
				}
			}
		}
	]
}
```

considering this information, to fix the issue one can either ask back-end to return onyx key with `personalDetailsList` in the `AddComment` call or, for a front-end only fix, use the data from initial `AddComment` response, extract all `targetAccountIDs` and create an empty object of `personalDetailsList` form (like the one above) with default data then merge it to onyx right after `AddComment` call succeeded.
